        <h2>1.Rise and Shine</h2>
        <p>Start your day by waking up early to maximize productivity. A consistent wake-up time can regulate your body's internal clock.</p>
        <p> <strong>Tip: </strong>place your alarm clock away from your bed to avoid hitting snooze repeatedly.</p>
        <h2>2.Hydration Matters</h2>
        <p>Drick a glass of water as soon as you wake up to kickstart your metabolism and rehydrate your body after hours of sleep.</p>
        <img src="kabizlik-poliklinigi-02.png" alt= "drinking watter" >
        <h2>3.Exercise for Energy</h2>
        <p>Engage in a morning workout routine to boost your levels and engance mental clarity throughout the day.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>30 minutes of yoga or stretching</li>
            <li>20-miute brisk walk or jog</li>

        </ul>
        <h2>4.Minndfulness and Meditation</h2>
        <p>Practice mindfulness or meditation for a few minutes to reduce stress and improve focus. Deep breathing exercises can help center your mind.</p>
        <p><strong>Tip: </strong>Use guided meditation apps for beginners.</p>
        <h2>5.Breakfast: Fuel Your Day</h2>
        <p>Never skip breakfast! A nutritious morning meal provides essential nutrients and energy for the day ahead.</p>
